        ],
        [
          "Regression",
          "Higher Education",
          "Problem-Based Learning",
          "344 students\n2472 enrollments",
          "Multiple courses in a Medical School (2014/2015 to 2017/2018)",
          "LMS logs\nCourse Grades",
          "Winne’s SRL Model",
          "[OLA_1, OLA_2, OLA_3, OLA_4, OLA_5, OLA_6, OLA_7, OLA_8, LALA_1, LALA_2, LALA_3, LALA_4, ORS_1, ORS_2, ORS_3, ORS_3, ORS_4, LARS_1, LARS_2, LARS_3, LARS_4, LARS_5, LARS_6, LARS_7, LARS_8]",
          "Each activity on Moodle was mapped into a learning-related activity:\n\nOLA: Overall LEvel of Activity, \n\nLALA: Learning action Specific Level of Activity\n\nORS: Overall Regularity of Study\n\nLARS: Learning Action Specific Regularity of Study.\n\nEach row refers to an enrollment",
          "Mixed Effect Linear Model (USing OLA),\nMLALA, MORS, MLARS, MFinal",
          "{Conditional RSquared: 0.726 - MLALA}",
          "NA",
          "NA",
          "Model results showcase that using Logs does not fully capture all learning activities, as learning activity and regularity explain very little differences in final grade. \n\nSame pedagogical model (PBL in this case) may not be portable across different couses. \n\nLearner characteristics (Internal conditions) explain most of the variance in performance rather the external conditions being considered (couyrse random effect and logs). ",
          "A lot of the curriculum relies on Problem-Based Learning Approaches.\n\nThere is a conscious effort to only include rpedictors obtainable from the LMS.\n\nAuthors create multiple mixed effect linear models on differente feature sets to select the most important predictors for a final model. User and Course were random effect.\n\nLALA features marginally get better results on Considtional RSquared but, overall, the feature sets seem relatively equivalent as performance does not vary significantly.\n\n\nOnly a very small portion of the variance (3% to 5%) in the final grade could be explained by the model.\n\n\n",
          "Homogenous set of courses (PBL).\n\nWould benefit from additional data sources than just LMS alone.\n\nData only captures a portion of the PBL learning process.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 5
    }
  ],
